    <div class="flickrentry entry">
        <h4>&#8220;DNTN XING&#8221;</h4>

        <a href="http://flickr.com/photos/groovymother/469052564/"><img class="flickrphoto" alt="&#8220;DNTN XING&#8221;" src="http://farm1.static.flickr.com/172/469052564_e3f487a1dc_m.jpg" height="180" width="240" /></a>

        <p>
            <p>Piss-poor information design from the MBTA.  &quot;Downtown Crossing&quot;, the station that links the Red, Orange and Silver lines, is abbreviated to the meaningless &quot;DNTN XING&quot; on this service map.  (Spotted on the wall at Copley Station)</p>
        </p>

